Yahya Jammeh (File: AFP) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; Footage of Gambian leader Yahya Jammeh refusing to step down after initially conceding defeat in the west African country's elections last week has gone viral on social media.Jammeh announced on Friday that he would no longer accept defeat, a development&nbsp; viewed by many as likely to plunge Gambia into turmoil."I accepted the results then, believing that what was presented was the will of you the Gambian people&hellip; I made it clear that I will never cheat in anything&hellip; In the same way also, I will never accept being cheated by anyone," Jammeh said.On December 2, Jammeh made a magnanimous concession speech on television and promised &ndash; to general surprise &ndash; a peaceful and swift handover of power to president-elect Barrow, sparking celebrations in the country.But on Friday, he pointed to errors which awarded victory to his opponent Adama Barrow with a slimmer margin than initially announced, claiming that numerous voters had not been able to cast their ballots."This is the most dubious election we ever had in the history of this country," he said."We will go back to the polls because we want to make sure every Gambian votes under an electoral commission that is impartial, independent, neutral and free from foreign influence," said Jammeh.Watch the video below.The Gambian leader has ruled the country for at least 22 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;His announcement was broadcast on state television.Meanwhile social media was abuzz on Saturday as Gambians reacted angrily to Jammeh&rsquo;s sudden U-turn. &nbsp;&nbsp;Yayha Jammeh of #Gambia No dictator, no invader, can hold an imprisoned population by force of arms forever. Liberation is coming!Pres Jammeh&nbsp;said his lost in election was Allah's will.But now he doesn't want to leave the office.Never mix politics with religion#GambiaYahya Jammeh must respect the people's will! His U-TURN and incumbency nonsense is over in Africa! The revolution is ripe and real #GambiaI call on the UN AU and the big organisation to put the man in order...we need peace in Africa and in Gambia over Yahya Jammeh decisionhttps://t.co/35WBMNxzSs was he just playing comedy of recent??? #Africa24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.